post_text:
Beginning Friday, May 29th, free breakfast and lunch will be available to pickup for anyone 18 and under at Batavia Elementary School in the front circle from 11am to 1pm.

Pickups will be every Tuesday and Friday.

The Tuesday pickup will include breakfast and lunch for Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday,

The Friday pickup will include breakfast and lunch for Friday, Saturday, Sunday, and Monday.

Meals are free for anyone 18 and under, and no registration or paperwork is required.

You may pick up for others should transportation be an issue.

post_text:
Any parents that placed an order for the Batavia Elementary Yearbook, production of the publication was delayed due to the state mandated lab shutdown from Covid-19.

Dingo Photography will be working with the publisher next week during their reopening. We will expect some more delays with the publisher due to the demand placed on production from so many other schools.

When books are received, Dingo Photography will work with BES to inform parents that their orders are in and parents can pick up at the Dingo Main Street Location and will also have Saturday pickup available.

Dingo Photography thanks you for your patience.

post_text: This is the final photo from a very impromptu social distancing YMCA photo series taken today at the end of food service deliveries. Sending a huge thank you heading into this holiday weekend to everyone who has been involved with keeping things going during this time of remote learning. Cafeteria staff, paras, bus drivers, custodians, teachers, coaches, admins, parents, students...everyone! This has been tough for sure, but as a Batavia community we are rising to the challenge. Keep up the great work social distancing, wash those hands, and keep taking care of one another. We’ve got this!

post_text:
Batavia Local Schools will be closed beginning Friday, March 13, 2020, and will remain closed through April 3, 2020.

At this point we anticipate a return to school date of Monday, April 6, 2020. Please be aware that this date is subject to change by order of the Governor.

This closure is in response to Governor Mike DeWine's announcement that all schools will be closed for three weeks, beginning Monday, March 16th.

More information regarding learning from home, spring events, extracurriculars, and food service will be forthcoming.

This continues to be a very fluid situation, and we appreciate your patience and partnership during this challenging time.

Keith

post_text: Not sure why everyone looks so serious :) Awesome first planning meeting for the new buildings! Mark you calendars for a community wide school building construction-visioning meeting on December 4th at BHS from 5:15 to 6:45.

post_text:
So, we realized about a year too late that the twitter connection to facebook was severed...and all this time we thought our messages were going out to facebook!

Anyways, we are going to be making regular posts to facebook again....please note, the facebook page is not monitored or moderated for questions or used as a dialogue tool...please direct any questions you have to the buildings. Thanks!

P.S. we created a District Instagram account (finally, right?) You can find it at: bataviaschools
